tivecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/</intellectualRights><additionalInfo>San Diego Natural History Museum Entomology Department (SDNHM-SDNHM)</additionalInfo><associatedParty><individualName><surName>Horsley</surName><givenName>Pamela</givenName></individualName><positionName>Collections Manager</positionName><electronicMailAddress>phorsley@sdnhm.org</electronicMailAddress></associatedParty><associatedParty><individualName><surName>Mojica</surName><givenName>Christiana</givenName></individualName><positionName>Project Manager</positionName><electronicMailAddress>cmojica@sdnhm.org</electronicMailAddress></associatedParty><abstract><para>&lt;p&gt;Collection is heavily focused on the SW USA and NW Mexico, particularly the peninsula of Baja California. Notably strong collections of Lepidoptera and Neuroptera. The median date of specimen acquisition is 1957 with collections ranging from 1905 to present day. Current and near future collection priorities will focus on underrepresented areas in Baja California, particular inland and coastal dunes.&lt;/p&gt;</para></abstract></collection><collection identifier="5e7df386-c816-4437-888e-e97d8d211ed7" id="129"><alternateIdentifier>https://ecdysis.org/collections/misc/collprofiles.php?collid=129</alternateIdentifier><parentCollectionIdentifier>UM</parentCollectionIdentifier><collectionIdentifier>WRME</collectionIdentifier><collectionName>J. B. Wallis / R. E. Roughley Museum of Entomology</collectionName><onlineUrl>https://umanitoba.ca/agricultural-food-sciences/wallis-roughley-museum-entomology</onlineUrl><intellectualRights>https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/</intellectualRights><additionalInfo>J. B. Wallis / R. E. Roughley Museum of Entomology (UM-UM)</additionalInfo><associatedParty><individualName><surName>Gibbs</surName><givenName>Jason</givenName></individualName><positionName>Curator</positionName><electronicMailAddress>jason.gibbs@umanitoba.ca</electronicMailAddress><userId>https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4945-5423</userId></associatedParty><associatedParty><individualName><surName>Lee</surName><givenName>Wonhyo</givenName></individualName><positionName>Technician</positionName><electronicMailAddress>Wonhyo.Lee@umanitoba.ca</electronicMailAddress></associatedParty><abstract><para>&lt;p&gt;Invertebrate collection, primarily insects (pinned, slides, and fluid preserved) with good representation for Manitoba, Canada, and strengths in bees and aquatic beetles.&lt;/p&gt;</para></abstract></collection></symbiota></metadata></additionalMetadata></eml:eml>
